            0 => [
                'questionText' => 'What\'s the difference between fantasy and high fantasy?',
                'answerText' => 'First, setting: fantasy might take place on Earth or a place like Earth; high fantasy nearly always takes place in a fictional world, with its own history, creatures, gods, cultures, and natural laws. Worldbuilding is often crucial to high fantasy. Next, magic: high fantasy nearly always has some kind of magic by which its practitioners can control its natural laws. This magic might have strict rules or be poorly understood, it might be commonplace or vanishingly rare. Third, scope and stakes: high fantasy focuses on epic stakes and the battle between pure good and pure evil. A conflict in high fantasy might threaten the entire world. This isn\'t always the case; it\'s possible to have smaller-scale stories in a high fantasy world, but for the most part, these grand forces usually exist, even if they aren\'t the focus of a given story.',
            ],
            1 => [
                'questionText' => 'What are some of the tropes of high fantasy?',
