        'faqs' => [
            0 => [
                'questionText' => 'What are some examples of imaginative media?',
                'answerText' => 'In film and animation, the works of Hayao Miyazaki and Studio Ghibli, like Princess Mononoke and Spirited Away, are great examples of imaginative spins on fantasy. Terry Pratchett\'s Discworld series of books are another great wellspring of imaginative ideas. Ursula K. Le Guin\'s body of work, including the Earthsea series and the sci-fi Hainish universe books, have a ton of creative spins on their genre as well. On television, shows like Avatar: the Last Airbender, Good Omens, Stranger Things, One Piece, and Doctor Who all bring imaginative twists on their own genre to the forefront. Finally, video games like Minecraft and Roblox are all about creating a sandbox to showcase the creativity that players bring to them, which is the heart and soul of imaginative media.',
            ],
            1 => [
                'questionText' => 'What makes something imaginative?',
                'answerText' => 'The use of imagination, specifically to create something new, unique, and unexpected, is the hallmark of imaginative media. Whether that\'s a creative combination of genres that don\'t typically go together, an update on a classic idea or trope common to a genre, or an innovative twist that makes a tired concept feel fresh, imaginative media gives its audience a new perspective and sparks their own creativity!',
            ],
            2 => [
                'questionText' => 'What if I\'m not creative?',
                'answerText' => 'The promise of imaginative games is that they will help you harness your creativity--even if you don\'t think you have it! The game\'s concept, its rules, and the agency they give you will inspire you to come up with ideas that will surprise everyone, even yourself. Everyone can be creative, and an imaginative, collaborative tabletop roleplaying game is the perfect way to flex that muscle!',
            ],
            3 => [
                'questionText' => 'Do imaginative games have tropes?',
                'answerText' => 'Yes, it does! But it\'s difficult to pin them down. Part of the core of imaginative games and other media is that they subvert or defy the tropes of the genre they\'re closest to. But even that is kind of a trope in itself; imaginative media tends to be in conversation with the expectations of its genre, and will choose which tropes to use, which to reject, and which to mutate intentionally.',
            ],
        ],
