        'slug' => 'horror',
        'name' => 'Horror',
        'description' => 'Horror is a genre that explores fear both physical and psychological, letting people feel scared without putting themselves in real danger. It delves into dark themes like death, violence, monstrosity, and helplessness, creating a safe way to engage with transgressive topics. From ghost stories around a campfire, to big budget horror movies, to friends at a candlelit table in a dark room playing scary games, nothing captures the human imagination like fear!

Roleplaying games have played with horror from some of their earliest iterations, as games are uniquely immersive and experiential. People play scary RPGs with friends to feel the vicarious thrill of the danger their characters are in, and sometimes to help overcome their fears. Monsters, darkness, and death have been creeping around in the TTRPG hobby for decades, and horror and its many subgenres remain one of the most popular genres in games even today.',
