        'faqs' => [
            0 => [
                'questionText' => 'What makes games scary?',
                'answerText' => 'Games, especially tabletop roleplaying games, are uniquely scary because players often identify with their characters; they say what they\'re saying, they do what they\'re doing, and they feel how they\'re feeling. RPGs that focus on horror often make characters feel helpless, disempowered, panicked, endangered, and just plain scared! When this happens, it\'s common for those feelings to "bleed" over into the player, giving them the true horror experience.',
            ],
            1 => [
                'questionText' => 'Are horror RPGs safe to play?',
                'answerText' => 'The most important part of the horror genre\'s appeal is that its participants are actually safe throughout the experience, even if it feels dangerous and scary. Of course, it\'s important to recognize that horror deals with dark, uncomfortable, and transgressive topics that can potentially be triggering or harmful to individuals at the gaming table. For this reason, it\'s especially important to use safety tools, discuss boundaries before the game, and build trust and rapport with the people you play with to ensure everyone can get scared in the ways they actually want to!',
            ],
            2 => [
                'questionText' => 'What are the subgenres of horror?',
                'answerText' => 'With horror being one of the most popular genres of media (and TTRPGs are no exception!), there are tons of different flavors you can find a scary game in: survival horror, where players are just trying to stay alive with limited resources; psychological horror, when the horror is all in your head; slashers, where players are hunted by a ruthless and violent killer; eldritch horror, dealing with mind-breakingly ancient beings; body horror, dealing with the mutation and violation of the physical body; gothic horror, focused on monsters who are often allegories for social issues; and the ever popular zombie horror, about dealing with a plague of restless undead.

Of course, this is just a small selection of the wide variety of horror subgenres; many, many more are available for the fearless explorer.',
            ],
            3 => [
                'questionText' => 'What are some examples of horror media?',
                'answerText' => 'Here are just a few examples of horror media, all of which have directly inspired tabletop roleplaying games: the Alien franchise, Bram Stoker\'s Dracula, The Call of Cthulhu and other works by H.P. Lovecraft, Buffy: The Vampire Slayer, and Supernatural.',
            ],
        ],
