        'faqs' => [
            0 => [
                'questionText' => 'What\'s the difference between fantasy and gritty fantasy?',
                'answerText' => 'Where standard fantasy usually has clear-cut heroes and villains, lots of magic, and a brighter tone, gritty fantasy has more morally ambiguous or "gray" characters, lower, more limited, or more costly magic, and a darker tone. A fantasy hero might take a beating and be back at it the very next day where a gritty fantasy character needs rest, medical attention, and time to recover from their injuries. Fantasy might elide the politics, violence, or harshness of its world where gritty fantasy dwells on it, highlighting the grimy details of living in its world, even with fantastical elements.',
            ],
            1 => [
                'questionText' => 'How do I know if I would enjoy gritty fantasy?',
                'answerText' => 'If you like to explore the details of fantasy worldbuilding, like where a kingdom gets its food or what restrictions its laws place on magic users, you might enjoy gritty fantasy! If you like higher stakes even for heroic characters and dislike "plot armor," where protagonists seemingly never face lasting consequences for their dangerous exploits, gritty fantasy might be for you. If you enjoy questions of moral complexity and difficult decisions about the right thing to do rather than a clear and obvious good and evil, gritty fantasy has what you\'re looking for! The devil\'s in the details with gritty fantasy, so if you like to get down in the dirt with your characters, explore the struggles of their daily lives, and get into their heads and under their skin, you might love this genre.',
            ],
            2 => [
                'questionText' => 'What are the themes of gritty fantasy?',
                'answerText' => 'Some common themes include war, politics, the consequences of violence, power imbalance and wealth inequality (sometimes with magical power as a metaphor), humanity as a source of monstrosity (rather than external monsters), poverty, and the exploitation of people and resources.',
            ],
            3 => [
                'questionText' => 'What are some examples of gritty fantasy in media?',
                'answerText' => 'Books like Glen Cook\'s The Black Company series, Joe Abercrombie\'s First Law books, Scott Lynch\'s Gentleman Bastards series, and the Malazan Book of the Fallen series by Steven Erikson are all prime examples. George R. R. Martin\'s A Song of Ice and Fire books and the television adaptations Game of Thrones and House of the Dragon are also great touchstones for the genre. Sword-and-sorcery books and films like Conan: the Barbarian have plenty of gritty fantasy elements, as do films like The Dark Crystal, The Green Knight, The 13th Warrior, and The Seventh Seal. Video game series like Dark Souls, The Witcher, and Darkest Dungeon also demonstrate many of the themes of gritty fantasy.',
