    6 => [
        'slug' => 'survival',
        'name' => 'Survival',
        'description' => 'The survival genre is all about humanity\'s struggle against nature. Harsh environments, scarce resources, hostile creatures, and maybe even other people threaten its heroes, who must use their strength, wits, and knowledge to gather the resources to survive. Nothing is guaranteed; ready access to food, shelter, weapons, and tools rely entirely on the characters\' resourcefulness and ingenuity. If they can succeed, however, they can begin to build. Gradually, surviving can become thriving if characters get a chance to build on their own success. The promise of the survival genre is building a sustainable future.

Survival tabletop roleplaying games are very popular, and are in fact some of the oldest games in the hobby. They work so well because they emphasize advancement: new and better gear, stronger characters with more powerful abilities, and growing resources are extremely satisfying to acquire, rewarding to use, and easy to understand as direct improvements. Because characters in survival RPGs often start with little to nothing, every gain is an obvious improvement. The process of beginning with nothing and fighting your way to the top can be thrilling, and the sense of victory that comes with success feels earned. ',
