            0 => [
                'questionText' => 'What are some examples of survival media?',
                'answerText' => 'In film and television, stories about life-or-death situations where characters strive to survive are very popular! The Martian, Life of Pi, Predator, 127 Hours, and A Quiet Place all exemplify different facets of the genre. Reality television shows like Survivor, Alone, Running Wild, and Survivorman follow individuals or teams using their know-how and grit to survive in the wild. 

Survival is also an incredibly popular video game genre: Minecraft, one of the bestselling games of all time, is a survival game, and exploration and survival horror games like Valheim, Subnautica, and Don\'t Starve also focus on resource-gathering, crafting, and environmental dangers.',
            ],
            1 => [
                'questionText' => 'What do you do in a survival game?',
                'answerText' => 'Survival RPGs place you in the shoes of a character in a hostile environment who must struggle to gather the resources to survive, shelter, and defend themselves--if you\'re lucky enough to have shoes. You might have to fight or avoid monsters, collect valuable resources to craft or sell, or go into dangerous places to scavenge or salvage treasure. Over time, if you\'re successful, you may be able to improve your position, your gear, and your skills to attempt more dangerous (and more lucrative) expeditions, with the ultimate goal of not just surviving, by thriving.',
            ],
            2 => [
                'questionText' => 'What are the tropes of the survival genre?',
                'answerText' => 'The core loop of the survival genre is gathering resources, spending those resources to improve your situation, and leveraging that improved situation to gather better resources. Creating stone tools to harvest metal to make metal tools is a common example. There are often hostile forces to challenge players like monsters, other characters, natural hazards, and weather conditions. Crafting one\'s own weapons and tools is sometimes an element, but there might also exist settlements where players can buy, sell, and trade items. Day is often relatively safe compared to night. Characters might need to manage basic needs, like food, water, shelter, and warmth, before they can even consider other things. 

Ultimately, the promise of survival is conquering the environment, gathering the best possible gear, and mastering the world itself.',
            ],
            3 => [
                'questionText' => 'What kinds of survival games are there?',
                'answerText' => 'There are action-adventure survival games, which focus on exploration, hunting and fighting monsters, and possibly delving into dungeons for treasure. Weapons, armor, and magic (if it exists in the setting) are important resources. There\'s also survival horror, which prioritize fleeing from and escaping monsters, gathering enough resources and having a secure enough position to survive the dangers of the night, and solving puzzles before threats can find you. Post-apocalyptic survival games might blend the two, tasking players with surviving a zombie outbreak or alien invasion.',
            ],
        ],
