            0 => [
                'questionText' => 'What makes horror Gothic?',
                'answerText' => 'A focus on human passion over reason and the uncanny nature of the horror is the hallmark of the Gothic genre. Gothic horror lingers in the surreal and the inexplicable, with its frights and monsters doing double duty as metaphors for human flaws like greed, lust, and wrath. Grappling with harmful, self-destructive appetites and the temptation to monstrosity is an enduring piece of the Gothic genre even today. If your horror has a haunting ghost, hungering vampire, or overreaching scientist or artist, there\'s a good chance it\'s Gothic.',
