    11 => [
        'slug' => 'comedy',
        'name' => 'Comedy',
        'description' => 'Make \'em laugh! The comedy genre is about being funny, first and foremost. Whether it\'s wacky over-the-top slapstick, clever and biting political satire, black comedy tinged with darkness, or whimsical absurdism, comedy is all about playing on, misdirecting, and subverting the expectations of its audience to get the laugh.

Anyone who\'s ever played a tabletop roleplaying game can tell you it\'s nearly impossible to play one without some comedy creeping in; something about the nature of a group of friends gathered to play pretend games of imagination together lends itself to levity and humor. Even in darker-toned games, funny jokes, bits, and gags shine all the brighter. Some games, however, are dedicated to creating an environment especially conducive to hilarious antics. Some crazy games have an inherently absurd premise, others have rules that interact with play in funny or unexpected ways, and many silly games have fun, lighthearted mechanics and writing that elevate the act of play itself. ',
