        'faqs' => [
            0 => [
                'questionText' => 'What makes an RPG wacky?',
                'answerText' => 'Little to no emphasis on realism, a comic tone, and player empowerment are perhaps the three major elements that contribute to a game\'s wackiness, whether or not the rules intend it! The less grounded in realism the game becomes, the more absurd things become possible, without the need to justify or explain them. A comic tone encourages players and GMs to let themselves be silly, cut loose, and have fun with characters and scenarios. And player empowerment lets them try anything they can imagine, even if it doesn\'t make perfect sense, and gives them a chance to succeed. ',
