            1 => [
                'questionText' => 'What are some examples of wacky media?',
                'answerText' => 'Cartoons are without a doubt the best example: movies like Who Framed Roger Rabbit?, Space Jam, and Shrek bend the rules of genre and storytelling in a wacky way. Television shows like Spongebob Squarepants, Looney Tunes, Animaniacs, Rick & Morty, and Adventure Time all have a zany tone and "cartoon logic" where they casually break the laws of reality with regularity. Comedy movies like Airplane!, Monty Python and the Holy Grail, Austin Powers, and Anchorman gleefully go for wacky jokes over realism, as do shows like It\'s Always Sunny in Philadelphia, Arrested Development, and sketch comedy like I Think You Should Leave. There are even plenty of wacky and absurd video games, like Goat Simulator, Katamari Damacy, The Stanley Parable, and many LEGO video games.',
            ],
            2 => [
                'questionText' => 'Why should I play a wacky RPG?',
                'answerText' => 'If you want to release the constraints of realism and allow your imagination to truly run wild, embrace a more improvisational "yes, and" approach to roleplaying games, and not worry about telling a grounded, serious, down-to-earth story, you might enjoy a wacky RPG. If your primary goal is to hang out with your friends, play a silly game, and have some laughs, this style of game could be for you.',
            ],
            3 => [
                'questionText' => 'What if my game is too wacky?',
                'answerText' => 'Going all-in on absurdity all the time can definitely wear thin; most wacky games are designed to have peaks and valleys of humor and strangeness. Contrasting hilarious hijinks with more down-to-earth moments is the best way to make both types of play shine! Make sure you and your table all agree approximately where the tone of your game should sit, and play around that area, making sure to have quiet and simple scenes to counterbalance the high-energy zany ones. ',
            ],
        ],
