            0 => [
                'questionText' => 'Why should I play a game set in the modern world?',
                'answerText' => 'A modern setting helps ground the world in things you already understand, making it easier to play a character who feels like a part of the world. You already know about cell phones, the internet, and the country you live in--that\'s all stuff you don\'t have to figure out when you play a modern game! You can set a game in your own hometown, or a city everyone at your table is familiar with, and not require your game master give you an hour of exposition on the setting.

