            ],
            1 => [
                'questionText' => 'Is modern a genre or a setting?',
                'answerText' => 'It\'s both! As a genre, modern stories are concerned with the struggles of contemporary life: politics, social issues, and technology most especially. It\'s great for exploring those topics directly without allegory or metaphor.

Modernity can also be a setting or backdrop that still keeps that framing, but also injects another genre as well: modern fantasy might explore magic or monsters in a disenchanted world; modern horror could heighten the fears of our world we face on a daily basis; and almost every superhero story takes place in a modern world as well.',
            ],
            2 => [
                'questionText' => 'What is modern fantasy?',
                'answerText' => 'Modern fantasy is a subgenre of modern stories that explore the idea that even though the world feels mundane and disenchanted, magic still exists. Often, this magic is kept a secret, hidden from normal people, but sometimes it\'s fully out in the open--superhero media, for example, is a common form of modern fantasy. ',
            ],
            3 => [
                'questionText' => 'Can I play any game in a modern setting?',
                'answerText' => 'You\'re guaranteed to not be the first to try it! Exchanging a game\'s built-in setting for modern-day Earth is frequently among the first homebrews or hacks that people create for any game. Generally, it\'s not too difficult to do, as modern-day earth is the setting that people are the most familiar with! But games which are designed with a modern setting in mind are much easier to work with, as they don\'t make assumptions about things like the economy (how much money is a gold piece worth?), religion, technology, or geopolitics!',
            ],
            4 => [
                'questionText' => 'What\'s the difference between urban fantasy, low fantasy, and modern?',
                'answerText' => 'Urban fantasy is specifically a contemporary city setting with overt or covert fantasy elements. Modern fantasy has similar fantastical elements, but isn\'t necessarily set in a city. Low fantasy can be set in any time period, and indicates the fantastical elements are rare or secretive, though usually integrated into the setting. And the modern genre is simply set in the world as we know it now or relatively recently in the past or near in the future, with no assumption of fantasy elements at all.',
