        'name' => 'Eldritch Horror',
        'description' => 'Eldritch horror is the fear of the uncanny, the inexplicable, the unknowable, and the impossible. Sometimes known as cosmic horror, it deals with humans\' fear of their own insignificance, and the limits of our understanding of a universe which is greater and older than we can possibly comprehend. Author H. P. Lovecraft is often credited as the originator of eldritch horror with his Cthulhu mythos, including novels and short stories about slumbering elder gods and supernatural forces so ancient, terrible, and powerful, that even knowing about them is a danger to human sanity, let alone looking upon them.

