    22 => [
        'slug' => 'urban-fantasy',
        'name' => 'Urban Fantasy',
        'description' => 'Why should medieval society have all the fun? Urban fantasy is a genre that takes the fantastical elements like monsters, magic, elves, and dragons and brings them into the modern day. Blending magic, technology, old-world superstition and folk lore, and modern rational thought and setting it all in a familiar city, urban fantasy deals in contradictions. The genre blurs the line between the real and the fantasy world; sometimes magic is a hidden or secondary world concealed from normal people, sometimes it\'s an open fact of everyday life. Urban fantasy explores the tension between the traditional and the modern, the fantastical and the disenchanted, and the faithful and skeptical.

Urban fantasy is a much-beloved setting for tabletop roleplaying games. A modern-day setting is frequently the first adaptation that players make to a fantasy setting, and ready-made urban fantasy games offer players lots of options. This genre is often maximalist, retaining all the options from fantasy, including species, magic, and gear that would otherwise feel out of place in a modern city, and adding new technology, like cars, computers, guns, and even robots. Characters might be mundane, magical, or something in between, caught in the balance between the fantasy world and the realistic struggles of modern life.',
