            0 => [
                'questionText' => 'What are some examples of urban fantasy media?',
                'answerText' => 'Perhaps the most popular modern precursors to the urban fantasy genre are Stephen King\'s The Dark Tower series and Anne Rice\'s Interview with the Vampire. This gave rise to several popular book series, including The Dresden Files, Rivers of London, and Percy Jackson. Urban fantasy television is perhaps its most popular incarnation, such as Supernatural, Buffy: the Vampire Slayer, Sabrina the Teenage Witch, His Dark Materials, and Charmed. Some popular films in the genre are Highlander, Big Trouble in Little China, Hellboy, The Crow, and Onward. Video games, too, have several urban fantasy contributions, like the Persona, Shadowrun, and Shin Megami Tensei series, as well as Disco Elysium and The World Ends with You.',
            ],
            1 => [
                'questionText' => 'What are the tropes of urban fantasy?',
                'answerText' => 'The most common is a secret or hidden world, where fantasy elements coexist with the modern world, but normal people simply aren\'t aware of it. Only those who originate from the fantasy world or have been touched by it can access it, and it must be protected and kept secret from mundane people, who would either destroy or be destroyed by it. Another common trope is magitech, the combination of magic power sources and technological function. Urban fantasy often borrows mythological or folkloric plots and sets them in the modern day. It also frequently deals with themes of tension between the old and traditional and the new, disenchanted, skeptical, and contemporary.',
            ],
            2 => [
                'questionText' => 'Why should I play in an urban fantasy world?',
                'answerText' => 'Urban fantasy helps split the difference between a totally understandable mundane modern world and a completely alien fantasy world. It gives players a solid footing in the rules of real world, which are easy to grasp, but still offers the fun fantasy elements of magic and monsters that bring life and color to the genre. It\'s fun to imagine that beneath the veneer of our world, the wonder of fantasy still exists to those who know where and how to look.',
            ],
            3 => [
                'questionText' => 'What\'s the difference between urban fantasy, low fantasy, and modern?',
                'answerText' => 'Urban fantasy is specifically a contemporary city setting with overt or covert fantasy elements. Modern fantasy has similar fantastical elements, but isn\'t necessarily set in a city. Low fantasy can be set in any time period, and indicates the fantastical elements are rare or secretive, though usually integrated into the setting. And the modern genre is simply set in the world as we know it now or relatively recently in the past or near in the future, with no assumption of fantasy elements at all.',
            ],
        ],
